String objects are immutable. (once created its data or state can't be changed)
      String s = "Mahan";
      s = "Singh"; // yaha change ho jaega but heap mein "Mahan" bhi rahega
      System.out.println(s);

== operator reference dekhta hai value nhi. (non primitive ke case mein) // string is non primitive in java

## Comparing two strings in JAVA
   *equals() method compares the original content of the string.
   *public boolean equals(object another) compare this string to the specified object.
   *public boolean equalsIgnoreCase(String another) compares the string to another string, ignoring case.
   *equals() compares values, "==" compares reference not values.

sc.next() - input mein space ke baad ki cheeze nhi leta
sc.nextLine() - pura input leta hai space ke sath

## JAVA String methods
   toUpperCase(), toLowerCase(), trim(), startsWith(), endsWith(), equalsIgnoreCase(), charAt(),
   valueOf(), replace(), contains(), substring(), split(), toCharArray(), isEmpty()
   Ye saare methods nayi string bana dete hain purani wali wahi rehti hai kyuki string immutable hoti hai.

Everything that starts with a capital letter is a class.